course_title: SPECIAL EDUCATION PRACTICUM: EARLY ADOLESCENCE THROUGH ADOLESCENCE
description: Approved placement with a qualified cooperating teacher serving students with disabilities in any of grades 6-12, supervised by a qualified university supervisor. Includes observation and supervised practice in the field of special education and discussion focusing on reflection and application of special education theories to practical settings.

children: Declared in the Special Education BSE

linked_requisite_text: Declared in the Special Education BSE or Special Education: Teacher Certification MS
